  "commentary": "With SPX at 7105.62 sitting between the negative gamma pocket at 7115 (-3850.8M) and positive gamma wall at 7100 (+5126.9M), dealers are likely buying this dip as we're in PIN regime and approaching the amplifying zone. The thick positive gamma walls at 7100/7150/7200 should act as strong magnets, with dealers expected to fade moves away from these levels and provide stabilizing flow. Key levels: watch for acceleration if we break below 7100 support, but expect mean reversion back toward the 7150-7200 zone where dealer selling pressure intensifies.\n\nBottom line: expect the market to get pulled back up toward 7150-7200 with dealers providing supportive buying at current levels.",
